---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Terms — Latent"
  description="The terms that govern your use of the Latent website, our applications, and any purchases made through Latent."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="legal" id="main">
    <div class="legal-label">Terms</div>
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated 24 July 2026</p>

    <p class="legal-lead">These terms govern your use of the Latent website, our applications, and any purchases made through Latent. By using our website or our software, you agree to these terms.</p>

    <h2>Using the website</h2>
    <p>You&rsquo;re welcome to browse, read, and share Latent.</p>
    <p>Please don&rsquo;t misuse the website by attempting to disrupt it, interfere with its operation, compromise its security, or access it in ways it was not intended to be used.</p>

    <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>The Latent name, logo, software, design, writing, and other original content belong to Latent unless otherwise stated.</p>
    <p>Please don&rsquo;t copy, redistribute, modify, or use them without permission.</p>
    <p>Your photographs remain entirely your own. Latent claims no ownership over anything you create with our software.</p>

    <h2>The applications</h2>
    <p>Latent applications are licensed, not sold.</p>
    <p>Purchases and subscriptions made through the App Store are processed by Apple and are subject to Apple&rsquo;s standard End User License Agreement and App Store terms, together with these Terms of Use.</p>

    <h2>The Field &mdash; the Moment&rsquo;s community</h2>
    <p>The Field is a public space inside the Moment where you can publish photographs. When you publish, you keep every right to your work. You grant us only what is technically necessary to run the Field: permission to store, display, and transmit the content you publish, until you take it back or delete your account.</p>
    <p>Publish only work you have the right to publish. The Field is small and looked after, and these things do not belong in it: content that is unlawful or infringes someone else&rsquo;s rights; nudity or sexual content, violence or gore, or content that shocks for its own sake; harassment, hate, or attacks on people; spam, advertising, or content published to deceive; other people&rsquo;s private information.</p>
    <p>The app provides tools to report content and members and to block anyone whose work you do not want to see. We review reports promptly &mdash; objectionable content is acted on within 24 hours of a report &mdash; and we may remove content or end an account that breaks these rules, without notice where the violation is serious.</p>
    <p>You must be at least 16 to create a community account. You can delete your account at any time from inside the app; deletion removes your profile and your published work from the Field.</p>

    <h2>Website purchases</h2>
    <p>When products are offered directly through our website, purchases will be processed by our payment provider.</p>
    <p>Applicable pricing, payment, and refund terms will always be presented before a purchase is completed.</p>

    <h2>Refunds</h2>
    <p>Refunds for App Store purchases are handled by Apple through its own refund process.</p>
    <p>For purchases made directly through the Latent website, refund terms will be provided at checkout.</p>

    <h2>Availability</h2>
    <p>We build Latent with care, but we cannot guarantee that our website or software will always be available, uninterrupted, secure, or free from errors.</p>
    <p>To the fullest extent permitted by law, Latent is provided &ldquo;as is&rdquo; and without warranties of any kind.</p>
    <p>Our liability is limited to the extent permitted by applicable law.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>We may update these Terms of Use from time to time.</p>
    <p>When we do, the date at the top of this page will be revised.</p>

    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p>These terms are governed by the laws of Lebanon.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about these terms? <a href="mailto:contact@latentritual.com">contact@latentritual.com</a></p>

    <a class="legal-back" href="/">← Back to Latent</a>
  </main>
  <Footer />

  <style>
    .legal { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 140px 24px 120px; }
    .legal-label { font-family: var(--font-label); font-weight: 300; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.28em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber-dim); margin-bottom: 20px; }
    .legal h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 300; font-size: 40px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--text-bright); margin-bottom: 12px; }
    .legal-updated { font-family: var(--font-body); font-style: italic; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-ghost); margin-bottom: 48px; }
    .legal-lead { font-size: 18px !important; line-height: 1.75 !important; color: var(--text) !important; }
    .legal h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 400; font-size: 21px; color: var(--text-bright); margin: 40px 0 12px; }
    .legal p { font-family: var(--font-body); font-weight: 300; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .legal a { color: var(--amber); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light); transition: color 0.3s ease, text-shadow 0.6s ease, border-color 0.6s ease; }
    .legal a:hover { color: var(--text-bright); text-shadow: 0 0 16px rgba(232, 196, 160, 0.5); border-color: transparent; }
    .legal-back { display: inline-block; margin-top: 48px; font-family: var(--font-label); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber-dim); border-bottom: none; }
    .legal-back:hover { color: var(--text-bright); text-shadow: 0 0 16px rgba(232, 196, 160, 0.5); }
  </style>
</Base>
